cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.RO 

The paper presents a closed-loop control system for regulating insulin delivery for Type I diabetes patients. The approach is data-driven and uses robust model-predictive control to handle uncertainties in meal and exercise patterns. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.RO (Robotics). However, given the focus on control and the use of model-predictive control, cs.SY is the most likely sub-category. The use of machine learning and data-driven approaches also suggests cs.LG and cs.AI as likely sub-categories. The application to diabetes management could also make cs.CE a relevant sub-category, while the potential for real-world implementation in an artificial pancreas could make cs.RO a relevant sub-category as well.
